cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with the task of multilabel classification of diagnoses given clinical time series, which is a problem commonly addressed in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a strategy to cope with missing data in sequential inputs, which is a common problem in many machine learning applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and evaluates linear models and MLPs, which are commonly used in neural networks and deep learning, respectively. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are also likely sub-categories.
